100 g Bacon Strips
113 g Baby Spinach
1 unit Tomato
½ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
1 unit Gala Apple
28 g Pepitas
2 unit Egg
½ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
2 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
¼ cup Dried Cranberries
3 tbsp Sour Cream
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
¼ tsp Garlic Salt
2 unit Chicken Breasts

Before starting, wash and dry all produce.  Add 4 cups (8 cups) warm water to a small pot. Bring to a boil over high heat.Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-high. Using a spoon, lower eggs into the boiling water. Cook, 7 min for a runny yolk or 9 min for a set yolk.**Drain and rinse eggs under cold water until cool enough to peel, 30 sec.Peel, then halve eggs. Season with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, core, then cut apple into 1/4-inch slices. Cut tomato into 1/4-inch pieces. Add mayo, sour cream, 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) vinegar, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) garlic salt to a small bowl. Season with pepper, then stir to combine.Pat chicken dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Cook on one side until golden, 6-7 min. Flip, then cover and continue cooking until cooked through, 6-7 min.**Set chicken aside to rest, 5 min.Drain fat, then add bacon to the same pan. Cook, flipping occasionally, until crispy, 5-7 min.\*\*Remove from heat. Using tongs, transfer bacon to a paper towel-lined plate. Set aside.Reserve 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) bacon fat in a large bowl. Carefully discard remaining fat.

Add remaining vinegar to the bowl with reserved bacon fat. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine.When bacon is cool enough to handle, crumble or roughly chop into bite-sized pieces.Add bacon, apples, tomatoes, dried cranberries and spinach to the large bowl with dressing, then toss to combine.

Thinly slice chicken.Divide salad, chicken and eggs between plates. Drizzle DIY ranch dressing over top. Sprinkle with feta and pepitas.